##A supermarket owner in Hangzhou drives a land rover to deliver goods to residents who can't buy necessities for several kilometers

WECHAT goodlife225

Functional Introduction, the relentless years, there is love.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
This Spring Festival is the busiest Spring Festival for me to open a supermarket

Dictation / Mr Jim

Now, I make deliveries every day, too, in my Land Rover.
I delivered goods until 9:00 pm yesterday, I put the goods to the gate of each community, wechat group said a, and then they came down to take. Came home last night, ate, washed and went to bed, got up at 6:00 this morning to work again.
I've been in Hangzhou for 20 years. I've run a supermarket for 13 years.
Many supermarkets are run by my family. The supermarket industry is one of our local pillar industries. Although the business is not high-risk high-risk, a lot to worry about every day, but so many years of hard work, coupled with the help of the hometown people, the supermarket also let us live in a big house, a Land Rover.
This Spring Festival is the busiest Spring Festival for me to open a supermarket.
I, as the boss, opened more than a dozen supermarkets, big and small. Before, it was delivered by a Third-party Company. Now I have to make my own delivery. My wife has also started working as a cashier.
My staff have been on tenterhooks lately, with five hundred customers a day. They wash their hands many times a day, but they say they're still afraid. Some are too afraid to go home in case something hurts their family. But instead of going home, I miss my wife and kids.

Some of the landlords said, "don't go out and do business. I'll give you a free house. ".
The supermarket opens, is the risk, does not open, how does the community so many common people's Daily Safeguard?
I've been having trouble sleeping lately.

01
Driving a range rover to make a delivery, and his wife works as a cashier
I went back to my hometown on the 12th of the lunar month, but I couldn't stay. The more you watch the news, the more anxious you become.

In accordance with past years, how I also want to go back to Hangzhou after the 15th day of the first lunar month, the third day of the first lunar month I drove back with my wife.
My supermarket are community-based, the largest has more than 1,000 square meters, a shop has more than 20 employees. This time back, I focused on the two largest supermarkets, which have the greatest impact on the people around.

I let our staff can come back to work quickly, to insist on fresh supply, to ensure that rice, this time to the customer to not abandon.

As a result, our largest supermarket has only three or four employees. Some trapped in the home can not come back, some back, but only 200 meters from the supermarket in the district, because the district closed, only out, if out, not back.
Others say they're back, but there's no place to stay because the landlord won't let the tenants stay.
I let the staff who have no place to live in my home, now my home has lived in three, if necessary, everyone can be crowded to live. I also want to go to play a proof, trapped in the next community to pick up the staff, the matter has not been done, I have to try to hurry.
The staff has no food to eat, can't eat instant noodles every day. I asked a friend to help me. He opened a noodle shop near the supermarket. I asked him to serve US only in the classroom and cook for us every day.
By all means, only a few of US can function properly.
My partner is making a delivery, too

Although the passenger flow is only a quarter of the usual, but how can such a few enough?
My wife says she's GonNa be the cashier. Several other shareholders also said they could work as cashiers, as well as delivering and tallying goods, or whatever.
So we've got ten people in our biggest store.
I also started making deliveries in my Land Rover. Usually there is a third party distribution, and now they do not do, we do not send which?
Yesterday, I drove more than 20 kilometers to Laoyuhang, where dozens of households reported that there were no supermarkets nearby for several kilometers, and that the necessities of life could not be bought. I pulled a cart and put it far away at the gate of their residential area. It was a call and it was gone.

We do not increase the distribution of a penny, today we work hard, tomorrow we will be more recognized.

02
The outbreak changed the sales model, and now a lot of people are placing orders in groups
I told the staff that our XX shop is the only core guarantee for the lives of more than 20,000 residents in our area, and we should keep it. It's no exaggeration to say that another big supermarket nearby has closed, as have all the other small ones.

The other day, the relevant leaders came to us to encourage us to overcome the difficulties. Leaders said the store can not be closed, but also do a good job every day disinfection work, to give customers temperature.
I'd love to, but I can't even get disinfectant anymore.
I even tried to get some suits for the staff, and we're all at risk. But where can I get one?
Every day I open a shop, every day I think, this is gambling Ah.
On the health of our employees, on the health of our customers.
If one of these people goes wrong, we're GONNA have to close the store. I can't imagine what I'd do to them, to their families, if something happened to them.
To reduce this risk, we began to persuade customers not to come to the supermarket, to send messages on friends'circles and on wechat groups to remind them not to come, don't come, don't come, what do you want, we send it, even later, without a break.
This is the "non-contact shopping" , who do not touch who the best, the safest.
Our supermarket used to have delivery service, where customers placed orders through delivery platforms, which were delivered by delivery boys. There's an outbreak, and the delivery guy's gone. We'll just have the customers place their orders in the group, and we'll deliver them ourselves.
We already have built a cluster, each community in the vicinity of one, there are a dozen. We used to just release information about our products, but now it's a channel for customers to place orders.
We in accordance with the community, a group of construction, residents in the group reservations

Before, there weren't many of them. There were only a few dozen of them. Now we can tell you in the group to buy things, each group is rapidly expanding, we pull people each other, each group has hundreds of people.
We tell everyone, in the group head long, to buy things, address, telephone are written clearly, we in accordance with the district centralized distribution to the district gate, we then in batches from.
At present our goods compare some to buy vegetables the APP, calculate is quite complete, the price is also relatively affordable.
Direct delivery of goods ordered by the owner

This outbreak is going to change a lot of people's lives, and I think we're going to have a big change in our sales model. Our own power is limited, hope that the government in promoting "non-contact shopping" can also give us certain support.
In a few days, we may not open the supermarket, all home delivery.
With fewer and fewer supplies, farmers prefer to rot in the fields and not go out
And that's not all.
We don't know when the epidemic will end, when the out-of-town staff can come back, can not come back their wages or to pay, certainly to pay. The rest of the staff, are now several times the salary, and a day 12-hour work, do not know how long.
Even if we can get through all of this, our upstream channels are getting narrower.
Toto is our buyer. These days he drives to buy vegetables.
Tell me more, as in the past, vegetable wholesale market is 24 hours a day, logistics in and out, even cars have no place to park. Now only open three or four hours at night, to buy a few sparse people, the market opened at 1 am, 4 am after no one.
Many gardeners would rather rot their vegetables in the fields than cut them and never go out. Anji County's bamboo shoots, Kentoku's strawberries, all the same, many of them rotten. The market is getting less and less food.
Less than 40% of the market where Doddo used to shop now has more than 100 suppliers. They turn it off after a while because they have to get home. Most of them live next to the market, and landlords say that if you're late, you can't get in. Some of the landlords said, "don't go out and do business. I'll give you a free house. ".
Our vegetable suppliers, which used to have a steady 40, now only operate around 15. Used to be choosy. Now it's just whoever's still open.
Vegetables are more expensive, according to the past seven days eight vegetable prices have fallen back to normal. Now it's up about 40% in general, and leafy vegetables in particular.
It's not just the vegetable market. These days we go to stock, frozen market has closed, dry goods market only 30% open, fruit market more than half do not do business, even meat is.
In the past, the market pulled 10 carloads of pork a day, and gave us this kind of buyer. Now it pulls one carload of pork a day. How can you say it is not expensive?
We fear that if it continues, suppliers will become fewer and fewer, and supply capacity will be progressively depleted. We won't be able to get it if we want to open a shop.
Like we can not get goods, the common people have no rice, no salt, no vegetables, how to do?

We fear that if it continues, suppliers will become fewer and fewer, and supply capacity will be progressively depleted. We won't be able to get it if we want to open a shop.
Like we can not get goods, the common people have no rice, no salt, no vegetables, how to do?
